JOHANNESBURG - Parliament's Portfolio Committee on Home Affairs has adopted terms of reference for an inquiry into the citizenship of the Gupta family. The committee will now thoroughly investigate how the controversial family became citizens so quickly. LISTEN: Do they or don't they? Another flip-flop on Gupta citizenship The probe is part of broader investigations into state capture. The committee will gather evidence from the Home Affairs Department and the public. Documents of foreign employees of Gupta-owned companies will also be investigated. eNCA